            "$x < 9$",
            "$x > 9$",
            "$-1 < x < 9$"
          ],
          "correctIndex": 0,
          "explanation": "Base $2 > 1$ keeps the direction: $x - 1 < 2^{3} = 8$, so $x < 9$. But the log needs a POSITIVE argument: $x - 1 > 0$, i.e. $x > 1$. Both together: $1 < x < 9$ — forgetting the domain is the whole trap.",
          "check": [
            "1 + 2**3 == 9",
            "log(8, 2) == 3"
          ]
        },
